.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATETIME.DAY" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDateTime.day \- Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.day
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]day\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] instances returns a positive integer
representing the 1\-based day index in the month of this date, which is
the same day number you would see on a calendar.
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]day\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
Use the \f[CR]with()\f[R] method to create a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] object with the desired new value.
.PP
For general information and more examples, see
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.day\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using day
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq); \f[I]// ISO 8601 calendar\f[R]
console.log(dt.day); \f[I]// 1\f[R]
.EE
